1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 What is Parliament?

The Parliament of India is the legislature of the Union.

It consists of:

1️⃣ President
2️⃣ Lok Sabha
3️⃣ Rajya Sabha

📌 Parliament = President + Two Houses.

🔵 Lok Sabha (House of the People)
Lower House
Represents people directly
Members elected directly
Maximum Strength:
552 (constitutional limit)

Current elected strength generally:

543 elected seats
Term:
5 years (unless dissolved earlier)
🔴 Rajya Sabha (Council of States)
Upper House
Permanent House (never dissolved)
Maximum Strength:
250
238 elected
12 nominated by President
Term:
Members serve 6 years
One-third retire every 2 years
🔹 Presiding Officers
Lok Sabha → Speaker
Rajya Sabha → Vice President (Chairman)
🔹 Functions of Parliament
1️⃣ Legislative Functions
Makes laws
2️⃣ Financial Functions
Passes budget
Controls public money
3️⃣ Executive Control
Questions government
No-confidence motion
4️⃣ Constitutional Functions
Amends Constitution
🔹 Difference Between Lok Sabha & Rajya Sabha
Feature	Lok Sabha	Rajya Sabha
Nature	Temporary	Permanent
Term	5 years	6 years
Dissolution	Yes	No
Money Bill power	More	Limited

